# Keep shell scripts and Git hooks LF so /bin/sh runs them on Linux/macOS
# regardless of a contributor's core.autocrlf setting (a CRLF hook fails with
# "/bin/sh^M: bad interpreter").
#
# Deliberately scoped: the rest of the repo intentionally uses CRLF blobs
# (rustfmt is pinned to newline_style = "Windows"), so this does NOT set
# `* text=auto` — Rust sources are left untouched.
.githooks/** text eol=lf
*.sh         text eol=lf
